      "content": "exactly. it's not even a \"leap\" if you look at how much data they have on us now. if they can use an algorithm to tell exactly what will make someone click a link, why wouldn't they use wearable patterns to influence how people act in real life? like, if a certain plaid grain can trigger a low-level trance or a sense of calm/compliance, it's the perfect way to keep the masses docile without anyone even knowing they're being controlled. it's just hidden in plain sight. don't you think there's a way they could be testing this kind of thing in mainstream fashion right now?",
